            <title>[FLINK-26741] CheckpointIDCounter.shutdown should expose errors asynchronously</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-26741</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;CheckpointIDCounter.shutdown&lt;/tt&gt; should return a &lt;tt&gt;CompletableFuture&lt;/tt&gt; exposing errors if anything happens to enable retrying of the cleanup.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All implementations should also work in an idempotent fashion, i.e. nothing should happen if the artifact was already deleted.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This bug is not considered a 1.15 blocker because unit tests rerunning the shutdown worked properly already, i.e. in the worst case (of an error) we would just miss to clean up right now.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
